25.6. Member Equity Tracking Feature

  


Requirements

The Phase 1 spec originally included special tracking and calculations for member equity, but that has been removed in the interest of scope reduction. The design spec has been moved here as an optional add-on that could be implemented in the future if the need would arise. In the meantime, a user report to show equity dollar amounts.

  


Estimated Cost: possibly $1,000-2,000 

  


Spec:

  


  * Contact Record:
    * Member Details Section:
      * Default Member Equity % (optional; number; 2 decimals; if set, this is used to calculate the Equity amount that is taken off of the "Total Buyer Payment $" (post-discount) for each Delivery Ticket from this Member; visible to and editable for only users with the "Manage Financials" Permission) 



  


  


  * Delivery Ticket Record:
    * Delivery Ticket Overview section:
      * Ticket # ...
        * when set, the following are also subsequently set:
          * "Member": based on the Member ID portion of the Ticket #;
          * "Member Payment Terms": defaults to the "Default Member Payment Terms" from the selected Member's Contact record;
          * "Member Equity %": to the "Default Member Equity %" from the selected Member's Contact record;



  


  


  * Member Financials section:
    * Post-GemWood Fee Subtotal $ (hidden; read-only macro used for calculations; dynamically displays the value of "Ticket Value $" \- "GemWood Lumber Brokerage Fee $")
    * Member Equity % (visible if the selected Member's Contact record has a non-zero value in the "Default Member Equity %" field; number; 2 decimals; with the following special behaviors:
      * displays the value of the "Default Member Equity %" from the selected Member's Contact record as of the time that the Member was selected on the Delivery Ticket and does not automatically change if the default settings is updated;
      * editable and required for users with the "Manage Financials" Permission; read-only for all other users)
    * Member Equity $ (visible if the selected Member's Contact record has a non-zero value in the "Default Member Equity %" field; read-only macro; number; 2 decimals; with the following special behaviors: 
      * displays the rounded value of "Member Equity %" * "Ticket Value $", or blank if = 0;  
      * displays in gray text with "(Pending)" suffix until Delivery Ticket Status = "Closed", at which point it displays in standard black text)
    * Post-Equity Subtotal $ (hidden; read-only macro used for calculations; dynamically displays the value of "Post-GemWood Fee Subtotal $" \- "Member Equity $"; blank if "Member Equity $" = 0)
    * Original or Estimated Member Subtotal $ (hidden; read-only macro used for calculations; dynamically displays the value of one of the following: 
      * "Post-Equity Subtotal $" if non-blank; 
      * otherwise, "Post-GemWood Fee Subtotal $")



  


  


  * Payment Record | Member Payment Detail Screen:
    * Ticket Details section: 
      * Member Equity $ (visible if "Member Equity $" on the corresponding Delivery Ticket ≠ blank or zero; auto-set and read-only; displays the "Member Equity $" from the corresponding Delivery Ticket; dynamically displays in gray font if "Delivery Ticket Status" ≠ "Closed")



  


  


  * Configure Payment Terms Report:
    * Columns:
      * Narrow blank spacer column, visible if "Show Sample Calculations" checkbox is checked
      * Sample Equity % (visible if "Show Sample Calculations" checkbox is checked; displays the value from the corresponding filter; green font) 
      * Calculated Equity $ (visible if "Show Sample Calculations" checkbox is checked; displays the calculated amount for the row; purple font) 



  


  * Filters:
    * Sample Equity % (visible and optional if "Show Sample Calculations" checkbox is checked; number; 2 decimals; defaults to "0.00") 



  


  


  * Member Payment Printout Page:
    * Ticket Details section:
      * Member Equity $: (visible if "Member Equity $" is visible on the Payment): <Member Equity $ from the Payment> (displays in gray font if "Delivery Ticket Status" ≠ "Closed") 



  


  


  * Other:
    * Member Payments Overview notes
